{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Hsu, Chen, and Todd trained college students in Taiwan to practice speaking with Intelligent personal assistants (IPA) Amazon Alexa by asking questions, searching for word definitions, and playing interactive games.",
    "After seven Alexa courses, there was an obvious improvement in these students' Test of English for International Communication (TOEIC) speaking tests.",
    "Researchers attribute the improvement to reasons that these students are able to chat with IPA in an appropriate context and fix their faults based on IPA's reaction [9].",
    "TPBOT, a task-oriented chatbot developed to help the preparation of TOEIC speaking tasks, also demonstrates its ability to enhance learner's scores.",
    "While the average speaking grade of the control group students who only self-learned with traditional TOEIC materials did not have an obvious change, the average speaking grades of the experimental group students increased by around 65 scores [10].In addition to making up for the lack of human experts' assistance, another benefit of AI-assisted speaking learning is reducing learner's speaking anxiety."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
